You're the one that needs to take a tape measure out to a bay window again.
It is a full 1 1/2". My 79 Westy is parked right outside. I've double
checked this measurement just now. It is 1 1/2".  Another reason why
"theory" has to take a back seat to actual testing. You seem to think that
sticking your finger outside the bus is going to tell you all you need to
know about if the bay window scoops ram air or not. Do some actuall
vacuum/pressure testing and you'll see they do a very good job. Again,
"theory" holds no ground to actual testing. If you don't understand that,
then i'm very sorry for you.

> Sorry, but I just can't believe that you would recommend dirt road driving
